<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/407.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Reid</persName>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d117fn1">Repeated to
                                Persia.</note></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-01"><hi rend="italic">December 1,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to department’s telegram 20th, you will inform foreign office
                            majority powers participating opium conference have agreed deference to
                            China’s wishes to postpone meeting until February 1. Also state that
                            this Government would appreciate early reply of Government to which you
                            are accredited.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>